owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

SaleCreated(address,address).notice: Emitted when a new sale is created

StatusChanged(address,uint8).notice: Emitted when a new sale is created

feePaid(address).notice: A mapping of wallet addresses to a flag for whether they paid the fee

getSale().notice: Returns the sale of the caller

getSaleByOwner(address).notice: Returns the sale of a given owner

launched(address,uint256,uint256).notice: To be called by a sales "finalize()" function only

launchingFeeInTokenA().notice: Returns the launching fee in the partner token

launchingFeeInTokenB().notice: Returns the launching fee in the raised token

onStatusChange(uint8).notice: Callback from reflex sale for event emission

resetFee(address).notice: Reset fee paid status of an account

sales(address).notice: A mapping of sale owners to the sales

setSaleUpdateApprove(address).notice: Approve the sale param update of the runner's sale
